7pm Hazlewood has the new ball and will operate from over the wicket

6.55pm The players line up for the national anthems. India's players draw big cheers.

6.53pm Rohit and Rahul are listed to open the batting for India. Axar is the only left-hander in their XI. Australia, too, have only one left-hand batter: Wade. No.11 Hazlewood is also a left-hand batter

6.40pm Alex Malcolm: Green has never opened the batting in professional cricket in any format. I can't even remember him doing it at club or junior level. But he has batted No.3 a lot in his youth and at domestic level in the BBL, Marsh Cup and Sheffield Shield cricket.

6.30pm Australia win the toss and opt to bowl. India pick DK over Pant and the hosts opt against rushing Bumrah back into action. Finch has confirmed that Cam Green will open the batting along with him for Australia. "This is a plan they have been discussing as a possibility for a while," Alex says.

India: 1 Rohit Sharma (capt), 2 KL Rahul, 3 Virat Kohli, 4 Suryakumar Yadav, 5 Hardik Pandya, 6 Dinesh Karthik (wk), 7 Axar Patel, 8 Bhuvneshwar Kumar, 9 Harshal Patel, 10 Umesh Yadav, 11 Yuzvendra Chahal

Australia: 1 Aaron Finch (capt), 2 Cameron Green, 3 Steven Smith, 4 Glenn Maxwell, 5 Josh Inglis, 6 Tim David, 7 Matthew Wade(wk), 8 Pat Cummins, 9 Nathan Ellis, 10 Adam Zampa, 11 Josh Hazlewood

Finch: Everything we do is in the build-up to the World Cup and it's about getting a bit of information. I think you need to be tested and every time you come to India regardless of the team they put out, it's a challenge. We're bowling first and there might be dew around.

Rohit: Every game gives an opportunity to correct ourselves and over the course of the last 6-8 months, we've learnt about what we need to do to win games. Looking at what happened in the Asia Cup, gives us a chance to reflect. We try do do that [pick the strongest team] but we have injuries. Harshal is back and Bumrah is not playing and will probably play the second and third game. I come back from the Afghanistan game and Pant misses out.

6.25pm David has received his maiden Australia cap from his Hobart Hurricanes team-mate Matthew Wade. Toss coming up in five minutes

Gokul Pradeep V: "Can't wait to see the explosion off Tim David's bat. Already licking my lips !"

Fasna: "I know I am saying an unpopular opinion but Pant should be backed over Karthik in this series at least. He should be batting at No.5. You know how a dangerous player he is when he gets going. I have a gut feeling that, if India are to win the WT20 down under, Pant will be the X-factor player"

Rahim Chagani: "No disrespect to India's Asia Cup bowlers but the return of Bumrah and Harshal add's a while new dimension to India's bowling attack. The best batsmen in the world struggle against Bumrah's yorkers and Harshal's slower balls so now it's just a case of getting them (and keeping them) match-fit for the World Cup. "

Issac: "I really hope the pitches are flat, bouncy and true like the Aussie pitches. Asia Cup, as much as it was entertaining, it was not ideal practice for the WC."

6.20pm ICYMI: India fast bowler Mohammed Shami has been ruled out of the series after testing positive for Covid-19. Umesh Yadav has been named as his replacement. India, however, will be bolstered by the return of Bumrah and Harshal from injuries. A fit-again Harshal has added more strings to his T20 bow by working on his new-ball skills and batting.

Jeetu Sangwani: "Pant or Karthik..?.this has been the most intriguing question after 'why katappa killed bahubali'?"

Kevin: "The 2 T20I series before t20 WC is more of an searching for the extra fast bowler, than a spinner... rest of the squad pretty much is complete... and also Pant or DK debate!"

6.15pm Ahead of the series, India captain Rohit Sharma said that Kohli will open in some games, but he still backed Rahul as their first-choice opener. On the eve of the first T20I, Rahul said that he's working on his strike rate. Strike rate has been the dartboard on Rahul's back ever since he said strike rates, when taken out of context, were over-rated

Siva: "Unpopular opinion, but I think Axar would be a better pick over Ash, considering Axar is more explosive with the bat, and also considering how Ash has turned into a complete defensive bowler of late, bowling only carrom balls to right handers.. Unless the opposition has 4-5 left handers, would want Axar playing over Ash.."

Azweer : "Is it going to be Rohit-Rahul or Rohit-Virat tonight?"

Damo: "Expecting one more ton from king Kohli today "

6.10pm Finally, finally, finally (in the Rock's voice), T20 superstar Tim David is set to make his international debut for Australia, having played franchise cricket around the world. It was always likely these three games in India would provide David the chance to make a debut for his second international team - he has played 14 T20Is for Singapore - but the injuries to Mitchell Marsh and Marcus Stoinis have made it all but certain.

And in the absence of Mitch Marsh, Steven Smith will bat at No.3 for the visitors.

Azweer : "Indian pitches will give Ashwin some good chances to warm up before the T20 WC."

Mustafa Moudi: "As Finch has retired from ODIs, hope he starts doing well in the only International Format he is active in."

Bishal: "All eyes on David but I will surely watch this for Cam Green what a talent he is "
